content.description: Looking directly at the High Electricity Boulder, there is an obvious large, blocky crack. Climb up that large, blocky crack. "That's it".
content.protection: A pad and a spotter will do.

content.description: Looking directly at the High Electricity Boulder, all the way on the far left of the boulder. 5 feet to the left of the upside down V is where it starts. "Bring your cajones and search for the hidden holds."

Looking directly at the High Electricity Boulder, this line is located on the far right of the boulder directly next to a "monstrous poison ivy plant that flourishes in summer". Climb the large crack.
content.protection: A pad and a spotter will do. SPOILER: you may want to avoid contact with the poison ivy plant.

content.description: Looking directly at the High Electricity Boulder, on the left side of the boulder is a distinct upside down V. "Highball your way up this crack to the top. Definitely exciting."
content.protection: 2 pads and a competent spotter. Prior beta could be a plus.

content.description: Located between "High Electricity" & "Yosemite Sam". The line starts standing atop the bulging outcrop at the base of the boulder. Work your way up without using the vertical cracks or the arete to the right. Committing 'stand up' moves on decent, small holds. "Quite scary for the grade."

Less than vertical with interesting easy+moderate cracks - clean rock.   Classic problem is the "High Electricity" crack. 

  Close to parking. 

  Walking off from the top often hindered by difficult vegetation. 

  SSW exposure and lack of trees make this nice for cool days in the afternoon.
